# ============================================================================
# RestoFlow .gitignore
# Multi-tenant Restaurant Operating System (RF-001 / M0A)
#
# Forward-looking: the toolchain below (Flutter / Melos / Supabase / Node)
# is NOT installed yet (M0A is documentation-only — see docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md
# and DECISION D-019). These rules exist so the repository stays clean once
# M0B (technical foundation) begins. See DECISION D-009 for the tech stack.
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# !!! SECURITY — READ THIS FIRST !!!
# SECURITY REQUIREMENT (DECISION D-011): no service-role credentials, no
# Supabase service keys, no shared restaurant password, and no .env files of
# any kind are EVER committed to this repository. Secrets belong in a secrets
# manager / CI secret store, never in Git. A leaked service-role key bypasses
# PostgreSQL RLS entirely and breaks tenant isolation (RISK R-003, CRITICAL).
# If you believe a secret was committed, treat it as compromised: rotate the
# credential immediately and purge it from history. See docs/SECURITY_AND_THREAT_MODEL.md
# and docs/OPERATIONS_AND_RECOVERY.md.
# Never use `git add -f` to force-add anything matched by the env/secret rules.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment & secrets (HIGHEST PRIORITY — see SECURITY block above)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
# Generic env-file forms — the `.env` / `.env.*` rules above only match names
# that START with ".env", so a non-dotfile env file (e.g. `supabasekey.env.local`,
# `staging.env`) would otherwise be committable. These catch any prefix so a local
# secret env file can never be staged by a plain `git add .` (RF-LIVE-001).
*.env
*.env.local
supabasekey.env.local
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.keystore
*.jks
service-role*
service_role*
*service-role*
*service_role*
secrets/
**/secrets/
*.secret
*credentials*.json
google-services.json
GoogleService-Info.plist

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dart / Flutter
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.dart_tool/
.packages
.pub-cache/
.pub/
build/
.flutter-plugins
.flutter-plugins-dependencies
.fvm/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
doc/api/
flutter_*.png
# pubspec.lock policy: COMMIT lock files for application/executable packages
# (apps) to guarantee reproducible builds; for reusable library packages the
# lock file is typically NOT committed. Decide per-package in M0B; do not add a
# blanket ignore here. (See docs/ARCHITECTURE.md for the package layout.)

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Melos (monorepo tooling — DECISION D-009)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.melos_tool/
pubspec_overrides.yaml

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generated code (build_runner output — DO NOT commit, regenerated on build)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.g.dart
*.freezed.dart
*.gr.dart
*.config.dart
*.mocks.dart
generated_plugin_registrant.dart
GeneratedPluginRegistrant.*
lib/generated_plugin_registrant.dart
# Drift / Moor generated database code
*.drift.dart
*.moor.dart

# RF-018 (RF018-B1) EXCEPTION — narrow, deliberate. build_runner codegen proved
# unreliable in the review/CI environment, so the SINGLE production Drift output
# is committed and CI no longer runs codegen. This negation re-includes ONLY that
# one file; it MUST come after the `*.g.dart` rule above for the negation to take
# effect. Do NOT broaden it: every other *.g.dart / *.drift.dart / *.moor.dart
# (including any test-only generated DB) stays ignored.
!packages/data_local/lib/src/local_database.g.dart

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IDE / editor (commit ONLY shared, intentional config)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace
# VS Code: ignore personal settings but keep shared, reviewed config.
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/launch.json

# Claude Code local agent metadata (e.g. .claude/settings.local.json) — never committed.
.claude/
# Local MCP server config may carry access tokens — never commit (root or nested).
.mcp.json
**/.mcp.json

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Operating system
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase (local CLI / backend — DECISION D-009; bootstrap under RF-013)
# `supabase/config.toml` IS committed (config only, secrets via env(...)).
# Real secrets live in gitignored *.env.local / *.env.keys — never in git.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
supabase/.branches/
supabase/.temp/
supabase/.env
supabase/.env.local
supabase/.env.*.local
supabase/.env.keys
.branches/
.temp/
# Supabase Auth JWT signing keys (config.toml: auth.signing_keys_path) — NEVER commit.
signing_keys.json
**/signing_keys.json

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Node tooling (scripts / CSV import helpers / CI utilities)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
.npm/
.yarn/
.pnp.*

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Coverage & test artifacts (see docs/TESTING_STRATEGY.md)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
coverage/
*.lcov
lcov.info
test/.test_coverage.dart
.test_runner.dart
test-results/
test_report.json
failures/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Platform build outputs (native shells — relevant from M1/M3 onward)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
android/.gradle/
android/app/debug/
android/app/profile/
android/app/release/
android/local.properties
# Monorepo apps (apps/*/android) — Android build artifacts + machine/secret files
# (ANDROID-001). The Gradle sources (build.gradle.kts, manifests, wrapper) ARE
# committed; only generated output, the local SDK path, and signing config are not.
**/android/.gradle/
**/android/.kotlin/
**/android/captures/
**/android/build/
**/android/app/build/
**/android/app/debug/
**/android/app/profile/
**/android/app/release/
**/android/.cxx/
**/android/local.properties
**/android/key.properties
**/android/**/GeneratedPluginRegistrant.java
ios/Pods/
ios/.symlinks/
ios/Flutter/Flutter.framework
ios/Flutter/Flutter.podspec
**/Flutter/ephemeral/
.symlinks/
macos/Pods/
linux/flutter/ephemeral/
windows/flutter/ephemeral/
web/.dart_tool/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs & local scratch
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
logs/
*.tmp
tmp/
.cache/
